article.description: Kyle Leufroy posted 18 points as Lehigh edged past Boston University 84-79 on Saturday.
article.headline: Leufroy scores 18 to lead Lehigh over Boston U. 84-79
article.linkText: Leufroy scores 18 to lead Lehigh over Boston U. 84-79
article.story: BOSTON -- Kyle Leufroy posted 18 points as Lehigh edged past Boston University 84-79 on Saturday. Lance Tejada had 17 points and six assists for Lehigh (17-8, 10-4 Patriot League). James Karnik added 14 points and Jordan Cohen had 13 points for the road team. Tyler Scanlon had 19 points, six assists and five steals for the Terriers (11-16, 4-10), whose losing streak reached four games. Max Mahoney added 17 points and eight rebounds. Alex Vilarino had 12 points. The Mountain Hawks improve to 2-0 against the Terriers on the season. Lehigh defeated Boston University 94-78 on Jan. 26. Lehigh plays Army at home on Wednesday. Boston University faces Holy Cross on the road on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
